===========================================================================
ASSESSMENT
===========================================================================

We ALREADY used the high-precision CODATA data where it matters:
  - PHYS-5/9: α from a_e using CODATA m_e, m_μ, m_τ
  - PHYS-10: α⁻¹ = 137.035999177 (CODATA 2022)
  - Modular search: all 17 SM targets at CODATA precision

What we DIDN'T do: extract real physical quantities from
each domain using CODATA inputs. But the table above shows
WHY we didn't: 6 of 9 domains have NO SM free parameters.
They use exact SI constants or material-specific quantities.

The SM parameters concentrate in Domain 2 (RG running)
and Domain 6 (CS/instanton). These are exactly the domains
where we already did the most work (PHYS-5, PHYS-9, PHYS-10).

CONCLUSION: Populating the domains with CODATA values confirms
what DISC-9 argues — the framework structure is independent of
parameter values. Most domains don't even CONTAIN the parameters.
The parameters live in the running (Domain 2) and the coupling
(Domain 6), which is where the search already looked and returned null.
